When you look at mature pages that have been changed, you often don't know what the changes are. It would great if there was a browse mode that showed you the changes since the last time you viewed this page. 

Yes, the implementation of this is database intensive, both structurally and during runtime. But I feel it would greatly enhance the useability of pages. As a reader of a page, you could focus on what has changed, rather than the whole thing. When you think about it, Word does a similar thing when you set it into "track changes" mode. 

Personally, I would only ever use the "changes since last login" mode. Because that's all I care about usually.

